thread.title: ANZ the next bank to talk profit
thread.title_full: ANZ the next bank to talk profit

author: news.com.au
title: ANZ the next bank to talk profit
text:
ALREADY disappointed by ANZ's profit growth and increased bad debt charges, investors will be seeking extra details during the lender's latest market update on Tuesday.
ANZ last week launched a $3 billion capital raising to help meet new rules to boost banks' protection against financial shocks, and issued its third quarter earnings numbers in the process.
The bank's cash profit rose to $5.4 billion in the nine months to June 30, putting it on track for a record $7.2 billion annual profit, but that was not as high as some had expected. ANZ also said its provisions for bad and doubtful debts had increased, partly due to stress in the resources and agriculture sectors. Despite releasing the numbers ahead of schedule, chief executive Mike Smith will still brief investors on Tuesday, and will likely face questions about the state of business confidence and the economy. Among other companies releasing financial results on Tuesday are QBE Insurance, retailer Dick Smith, pathology and radiology provider Sonic Healthcare and Sydney Airport.
